  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>Turkey's earthquake history is a long record showing that the same faults rupture in the same regions again and again. What that record tells us is clear: the question is not "will an earthquake happen?" but "how prepared will we be when it does?" Converting the lessons of the past into individual preparedness — choosing sound housing, having a family plan, keeping an earthquake kit — is the only way to shorten the painful recurring chapters of this history.</p>
